I can understand what you mean. At the time I was trying to really contrast the happy-to-lucky aspect of the the Whimsey theme park to the potential shadiness of the company. Yeah, their ultimate goal is to unify anthros and humans, but if something happened that could jeopardize the whole plan (like a certain anon discovering the anthros prematurely), then they'd have no reservations about eliminating the threat before word gets out. Basically, they wanted to break the news on their own terms, and tensions were high when Anon was suddenly dropped onto their laps.

Looking back at the earlier chapters, I do see things that I could have probably handled better in some spots. Wasn't sure how far I could run with the idea of Happiest at first, so I didn't plan ahead as far as I have been doing for a while now. I'm a little hesitant to ever touch past stuff apart from some minor formatting/spelling corrections, though, because changing the canon too much could throw other things off or confuse readers.
